article.headline: Colgate 66, Army 59
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Alvin Reed scored 15 points to lead Colgate to a 66-59 win over Army Wednesday night. Andrew Zidar added 14 points and Jon Simon 12 for the Raiders (12-14, 7-6 Patriot League), who have won four of their last five games. Colgate jumped out to a 4-0 lead and never gave it up. The Raiders led by 18 points with 6:02 left in the first half before settling for a 37-26 halftime lead. Army cut the deficit to three, 62-59, with 17 seconds remaining before Zidar and Jon Foss hit four free throws to seal the win for Colgate. Jarell Brown scored 18 points for the Black Knights (3-22, 1-12), who have lost 16 of 17. Matt Bell chipped in 17 and Cory Sinning added 12.
